{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"92281b1c-6960-4b37-b17e-f7069f9c14e7","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\n\nThe VSTest `--filter` flag becomes `--filter` on the **MTP runner**, but the operators change:\n\n| VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~X` | `FullyQualifiedName~X` *(same)* |\n| `&` (AND) | `&` *(same)* |\n| `Category=Smoke` | **`Category=Smoke`** *(same key, but see below)* |\n\nThe filter *expression* syntax is actually compatible, **but the invocation changes**. With MTP, the test project is an executable, so you run:\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest runner)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP runner) — same flag works via dotnet test\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThis should still work with `dotnet test` because the `--filter` is forwarded. However, if you invoke the executable directly:\n\n```bash\n./TestProject --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### 2. The real gotcha — Trait discovery\n\nxUnit v3 changed how `[Trait]` maps to filter metadata. Traits are now exposed with a **`Category`** key only if you use the **`[Category]`** attribute (new in v3), not `[Trait(\"Category\", \"...\")]`.\n\nTo make your filter work, either:\n\n**Option A** — Switch to the new `[Category]` attribute (recommended):\n```csharp\n[Category(\"Smoke\")]  // xUnit v3 native\n```\n\n**Option B** — Keep `[Trait]` and filter on the trait directly:\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n`[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` still maps to `Category=Smoke` in v3's filter, so this should work. But if it doesn't match, use the trait prefix form:\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&trait=Category%3DSmoke\"\n```\n\nWant me to update your test file to use `[Category(\"Smoke\")]` for v3 idiom?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"98207128-be24-4e9a-9178-0844fc45fdc1","outputTokens":600,"requestId":"340D:9F564:593C13E:615AE17:69F3FC35"},"id":"7c8a1cbb-5c4f-469d-847a-58e9992f9743","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:05:06.720Z","parentId":"05f3211e-d5c7-4a51-b429-f9bbc8b6ce4d"}
